  "title": "CRITICAL: Memory and Context Management Issues - Hotfix Tracking",
  "body": "## Critical Issues\n\nThis tracking issue consolidates the critical memory and context management problems identified in our production environment:\n\n- Issue #49: Context auto-compact functionality stuck at 0% completion\n- Issue #46: JavaScript heap out of memory crashes during large MCP operations\n\n## Impact Assessment\n\nThese critical issues are causing severe user impact across our platform:\n\n- **Context Auto-Compact Issue (#49)**: Tool becomes completely unusable on macOS platforms, with context management failing to progress beyond 0% completion, effectively blocking all user workflows.\n\n- **Memory Exhaustion Issue (#46)**: Complete Claude Code crashes requiring full application restart when processing large datasets, resulting in lost work and productivity disruption for users.\n\n- **Cross-Platform Instability**: Combined effect results in unreliable service delivery, with users experiencing frequent crashes and system freezes.\n\n## Resolution Strategy\n\nOur planned approach involves implementing a comprehensive memory optimization framework:\n\n1. **Immediate Hotfix Deployment**:\n   - Create dedicated hotfix branch for v1.0.72\n   - Implement progressive context cleanup with configurable thresholds\n   - Add streaming data processing for large MCP operations\n\n2. **Memory Management Enhancements**:\n   - Deploy 10MB default context buffer limits\n   - Implement automatic context pruning at 80% threshold\n   - Add memory usage monitoring and garbage collection optimization\n\n3. **Documentation and Configuration**:\n   - Create comprehensive memory optimization guide\n   - Provide configurable memory management options\n   - Enable manual context reset capabilities\n\nThis hotfix addresses the root causes identified in issues #49, #46, and relates to the broader stability concerns mentioned in #47.\n\n**Keywords**: memory exhaustion, context auto-compact, JavaScript heap, hotfix priority",
  "labels": ["bug", "critical", "hotfix", "memory", "documentation"]
}", "include_output_fields": ["number", "title", "html_url", "state"]}

