{"server_name": "GitHub", "category_name": "GITHUB_PULLS", "action_name": "create", "path_params": "{"owner": "mcpmark-eval-zl", "repo": "claude-code"}", "body_schema": "{
  "title": "HOTFIX: Critical memory optimization for issues #49 and #46",
  "head": "hotfix/memory-optimization-v1.0.72",
  "base": "main",
  "body": "## Summary\n\nThis hotfix implements comprehensive memory optimization solutions to address critical stability issues affecting Claude Code v1.0.72. The implementation focuses on resolving context management failures and JavaScript heap exhaustion problems that have rendered the application unusable on macOS platforms and caused complete crashes during large MCP operations.\n\n## Critical Issues Addressed\n\n### Context Auto-Compact Stuck at 0% (Issue #49)\n- **Problem**: Context management system completely fails to progress beyond 0% completion\n- **Impact**: Tool becomes entirely unusable on macOS platforms, blocking all user workflows\n- **Solution**: Implemented progressive context cleanup with configurable 80% threshold\n- **Technical Fix**: Added automatic context pruning and manual reset capability via `/memory-reset` command\n\n### JavaScript Heap Out of Memory (Issue #46)\n- **Problem**: Memory allocation failures during large MCP operations cause complete application crashes\n- **Impact**: Users experience data loss and must restart Claude Code frequently\n- **Solution**: Implemented streaming data processing with 1MB chunks and backpressure controls\n- **Technical Fix**: Added memory monitoring, garbage collection optimization, and 10MB context buffer limits\n\n## Documentation Changes\n\nThis PR introduces a comprehensive **Memory Optimization Guide** (`docs/MEMORY_OPTIMIZATION.md`) that provides:\n\n- **Root Cause Analysis**: Detailed explanation of the memory management issues identified in both critical bugs\n- **Optimization Strategies**: Step-by-step implementation of immediate fixes including context buffer management and MCP operation streaming\n- **Configuration Options**: JSON configuration schema for memory thresholds, streaming chunk sizes, and garbage collection settings\n- **Technical Implementation Details**: Progressive cleanup algorithms, backpressure mechanisms, and monitoring capabilities\n\nThe documentation serves as both a reference for the current fixes and a guide for future memory optimization work.\n\nAddresses #49\nAddresses #46\nTracked in #54\n\n**Keywords**: memory optimization, context management, heap exhaustion, v1.0.72 hotfix"
}", "include_output_fields": ["number", "title", "html_url", "state"]}

